<item>
            <title>[HBASE-12462] Support deleting all columns of the specified family of a row in hbase shell</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-12462</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently, HBase shell only support deleting a column of a row in a table. In some scenarios, we want to delete all the columns under a a column family of a row,  but there may be many columns there. It&apos;s difficult to delete the columns one by one in shell.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It&apos;s easy to add this feature in shell since the Delete have the API of deleting a family.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
